<task id="021" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>SendEmailStep wrapper — thin inline-mount wrapper for wizard step usage</title>
    <phase>Wave 1 — Engine + Wrappers + Sub-Components</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <blocks>071, 072</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, communication</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Thin wrapper (~30-60 LOC); semantic prop API translation; no new architecture. STANDARD is appropriate; the engine + validation contract carry the heavy lifting.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-02</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build the canonical `<SendEmailStep />` wrapper at `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailStep.tsx`. Thin (~30-60 LOC). Locks `mount='inline'`. Exposes a semantic prop API tailored to wizard-step usage.

    Wizard owns the "Send" / "Finish" button — wrapper just renders the composer; wizard calls `composerRef.current.send()` on Finish. Wrapper does NOT render its own action bar (the engine's ComposerActionBar returns null on `mount='inline'` per task 019).

    Props (FR-02):
    - `composerRef: React.Ref<IEmailComposerHandle>` — wizard holds the ref to drive imperative methods
    - `initialTo?: IRecipient[] | string` — initial recipient list (string for paste-from-Outlook source)
    - `initialSubject?: string`
    - `initialBody?: string`
    - `initialBodyFormat?: 'html' | 'plaintext'`
    - `associations?: IComposerAssociation[]` — record refs to stamp on the sprk_communication
    - `attachmentSources?: IComposerAttachmentSource[]` — wizards typically configure `['wizard', 'related']`
    - `wizardContext?: { uploadedFiles?: ... }` — passes through to WizardAttachmentSource
    - `authenticatedFetch: typeof fetch` — injected by host (NFR-02)
    - `onStateChange?: (state: EmailComposerState) => void` — wizard listens to update its Finish button enabled state

    Implementation: `forwardRef` → render `<EmailComposer mount='inline' mode='compose' ref={composerRef} ... />`. Forwards `composerRef` through.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer comfortable with thin-wrapper-with-forwardRef pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SendEmailStep.tsx` compiles + lint-clean. ~30-60 LOC. Locks `mount='inline'`. Passes through ref so wizard hosts can call imperative methods. Wave 5 wizard migrations (tasks 071, 072) consume this.
  </goal>

